- "Lighting up the field" means the players are still active;
- "2023 season" specifies the time period for the statistics.

- "High-earning players" refers to players with a total contract value greater than $10,000,000;
- "Significant contracts" are those that surpass the average annual salary of their team;
- "Exceptional team salaries" indicate teams with an average annual salary over $5,000,000.

- "Top performers" are defined as players with the highest number of home runs and RBIs in their respective seasons;
- "Top 5 highest-paid players" refers to the players with the highest salaries within their teams;
